1️⃣ Pradhan Mantri Jan Dhan Yojana (PMJDY)

Launched: 2014
Ministry: Ministry of Finance

Description of the Scheme:

Pradhan Mantri Jan Dhan Yojana is a national mission for financial inclusion that aims to bring the unbanked population into the formal banking system. The scheme focuses on opening basic savings bank accounts for every household so that government welfare benefits can be transferred directly, reducing leakages and increasing transparency.

Objective:
To ensure universal access to banking services such as savings accounts, remittance facilities, credit, insurance, and pension.

Key Features:

Zero-balance savings bank account

RuPay debit card

Direct Benefit Transfer (DBT)

Overdraft facility for eligible account holders

Insurance coverage

Documents Required:

Aadhaar card / any officially valid document

Passport-size photograph

Eligibility:

Indian citizen

Minimum age: 10 years

Person without an existing bank account

2️⃣ Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (PMAY)

Launched: 2015
Ministry: Ministry of Housing and Urban Affairs

Description of the Scheme:

Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana is a flagship housing scheme of the Government of India aimed at providing affordable and quality housing to the urban and rural poor. The scheme supports beneficiaries through financial assistance and interest subsidies to enable them to own a permanent (pucca) house with basic facilities.

Objective:
To provide “Housing for All” by ensuring access to affordable housing.

Components:

PMAY (Urban)

PMAY (Gramin)

Key Features:

Financial assistance and loan interest subsidy

Houses with basic amenities like toilets, water, and electricity

Credit Linked Subsidy Scheme (CLSS)

Documents Required:

Aadhaar card

Income certificate

Bank account details

Eligibility:

EWS, LIG, MIG categories

Applicant must not own a pucca house anywhere in India

3️⃣ Pradhan Mantri Ujjwala Yojana (PMUY)

Launched: 2016
Ministry: Ministry of Petroleum and Natural Gas

Description of the Scheme:

Pradhan Mantri Ujjwala Yojana is a social welfare scheme designed to provide clean cooking fuel to women from economically weaker sections. The scheme replaces traditional cooking methods using firewood and cow dung with LPG, improving health, safety, and living conditions.

Objective:
To promote clean fuel usage and reduce health hazards caused by traditional cooking fuels.

Key Features:

LPG connections issued in women’s names

Financial support for initial LPG setup

Emphasis on safety and cleanliness

Documents Required:

Aadhaar card

Ration card

Bank account

Eligibility:

Women aged 18 years and above

Belonging to BPL or eligible low-income households

No existing LPG connection in the household

4️⃣ Ayushman Bharat – Pradhan Mantri Jan Arogya Yojana (PM-JAY)

Launched: 2018
Ministry: Ministry of Health and Family Welfare

Description of the Scheme:

Ayushman Bharat – PM-JAY is the world’s largest government-funded health insurance scheme. It provides health coverage to poor and vulnerable families, ensuring access to quality healthcare services without financial burden.

Objective:
To provide financial protection against high medical expenses.

Key Features:

Health insurance cover up to ₹5 lakh per family per year

Cashless and paperless treatment

Nationwide portability

Documents Required:

Aadhaar card / Ration card

Mobile number

Eligibility:

Families identified under SECC database

Poor and vulnerable households

5️⃣ Beti Bachao Beti Padhao (BBBP)

Launched: 2015
Ministry: Ministry of Women and Child Development

Description of the Scheme:

Beti Bachao Beti Padhao is a comprehensive scheme aimed at addressing the declining child sex ratio and promoting the education and empowerment of the girl child. It focuses on changing societal attitudes and encouraging positive behavioral changes.

Objective:
To protect, educate, and empower the girl child.

Key Focus Areas:

Prevent gender-biased sex selection

Promote education of girls

Improve survival and protection of girl children

Documents Required:

Birth certificate

School enrollment proof

Eligibility:

Girl children

Parents, guardians, and institutions

6️⃣ Mahatma Gandhi National Rural Employment Guarantee Act (MGNREGA)

Launched: 2005
Ministry: Ministry of Rural Development

Description of the Scheme:

MGNREGA is a rights-based employment scheme that guarantees wage employment to rural households. It aims to enhance livelihood security while creating durable assets that strengthen the rural economy.

Objective:
To provide at least 100 days of wage employment per year to rural households.

Key Features:

Demand-driven employment

Wage payment through banks/post offices

Creation of rural infrastructure assets

Documents Required:

Job card

Aadhaar card

Bank or post office account

Eligibility:

Rural households

Adult members willing to do unskilled manual work
